value.0: You are not of our tribe we do not expect you to understand. Now run along and bother someone else.

We are ferocious defenders of the Wyld who call Greece our home. Our tribe, almost entirely composed of female Garou, and is renowned for its members' honor, ferocity, and attunement to the sacred.  You see Luna, in her aspect as Artemis the Huntress, created ourr tribe from she-wolves and appointed us to be protectors of the Wyld, defenders of women, and punishers of men.  We uphold these duties with grim determination.

Other tribes look askance at us Furies, who give away or kill our male children.  Many outside our tribe see the Furies as man-haters, but the truth is much more complex.  Although the tribe will tolerate male metis. We believe that women share a deeper bond with Gaia than any man can know, and see themselves as aspects of the Goddess incarnate.  In her name, we Rage against any insult to women, nature or the Goddess.  We accept the Triat and the existence of the Wyrm, but when it encroaches on our territory, woe be unto it

We maintain strong ties to ancient mysticism.  Our rites are complex and quite beautiful, and our Gifts and spirit allies reflect a primal connection to the Wyld.  Prior to any great test, a Black Fury will purify herself in a ritual bath in the open under the light of the moon, typically in a glade protected by the tribe.  This protection is taken very seriously - though the Wyrm must be fought, if the Wyld places are not protected then there will be nothing left after the last battles.  Our Kin are protected just as righteously, and are often active in their own right working for protection of wilderness and the rights of women though they still struggle with this.
We place a high value on our honor; even our hated rivals concede that the tribe can be trusted.  Although strong in character, we are few in number and our radical stance alienates many Garou.
Which clan would you like to know of?

They allow the Wyrm to encroach further upon the old places and try to pass it of as some kind of evolution.  They are merely servants of the destructive process which has defiled sacred place after sacred place.  Something must be done about them, and soon.

The Fangs still think that the accident of their birth can cause us to respect them and obey their commands.  They are wrong.  We watch these Fangs, and if any of these "heroes" interferes with our plans, we will crush them.
They are our silent partners.  Help them in any way possible, but watch them - there is something hidden behind their closed jaws.

We have seen these manipulative, sweet-talking Lords lie and cheat their way through history.  They have never kept a promise to the Furies, and they are continually selling our people out to the highest bidder.  Do everything you can to expose them for what they are, and when in doubt, fight.
We are sisters with them, in many ways, for they fight just as desperate a fight.  They would make excellent allies if they could see that our battle is the same as theirs.

Chauvinistic, self-centered, ill-mannered drunkards, every one of 'em.  A few of them remember Brigid and Rhiannon...but only a few.  Their women are very close to us in spirit.  If their men would only let us fight as comrades we would be a potent force against the Wyrm.

Fascist dogs!  They style themselves protectors, and claim that they are the only ones who take action.  For every step we take against the Wyrm, the Fenrir push us two back.  They must be stopped...or put down like the rabid dogs they are.
Noble and helpful, the only bad thing you can say about them is that they don't do enough.  We are growing tired o their placatory ways, as well...the rage of Gaia will not long be delayed.
Harmless street mongrels - but they know more than they let on.  Don't judge them by their smell; they can often be helpful, just like good watchdogs.
I am proud to be one of her choosen.
What else can you tell me about my sisters?
One day it will happen.
